<td width=50%><font color=white>Posted By: Bobarafius Rootanrun</font></td><td width=50% align=right><font color=white>2000-06-29 14:39:34</font></td></tr><tr>
<td colspan=2 bgcolor="#0000AF"><font color=white>Synge is a rare spawn wyvern real small dragon looking thingie.  From Sol A entrance walk down the steps and thru the side psg past the swinging axe trap then turn to your left and walk across the bridge there are 2 goblins and synge spawns right between them he is about lvl 24 me and 2 others royally kicked his arse but he just dropped obsidian bead hoop good earrings for ac til ya get diamondines or forest loops.  I used this belt til I got my fbss which was at 40 so if I would have to say this is one of the better in game belts. =)<BR>
P.S. I am using directions from the Lava entrance to Sol A not the one from Sol B to Sol A. o)</font></td></tr></table>
<BR>
<table width=100%>
<tr>
<td width=50%><font color=white>Posted By: Nazereth</font></td><td width=50% align=right><font color=white>2000-09-01 07:20:01</font></td></tr><tr>
<td colspan=2 bgcolor="#0000AF"><font color=white>From what I have seen while camping Kindle for hours and hours Singe is a roaming spawn much like Kindle. More times than not I have seen him or his placeholder which is general a fire goblin or inferno goblin but I have seen a shaman for his PH. And after I find the roaming PH I time him for roughly 20 minutes. He can be found from the area where the zone to sol B is and his pathing goes up the steps above the Kindle mines and down the hall to the right past the turn for Gabbie and EXG.If not stopped he will make it all the way to the bridge the leads out to the pit but will take a left to the cove and eventualy turn around and head back, he can stop for periods and have seen him spawn in several different spots (like five at least) but the path for him and his PH is the same. IMHO sit abobe the kindle pits and just invis and roam around and you will have him or his PH roam by. Hope this helps. His common drop is the Obsidian Bead Hoop. Pretty nice earing with two ac +3 agi +3 int sells for about 100 PP on Tareww Marr. Have sold about 20 in my days. I cant tell you his level but I think a 30 + can take him without problems from others. Good luck...</font></td></tr></table>
